   Orc Commander (2)<br>
   Orc Overseer (2)<br>
   Saruman, Servant of the Eye (2)<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(125)">Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul</a><br>
   Tower of Orthanc (2)<br>
   Coming for the Ring (2)<br>
   One of You Must Do This (2)<br>
   The Trees Are Strong (2)       </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Yes, the power of men.  Boromir and Aragorn carry the party, with Boromir using the horn as needed.  Bid carefully, remembering Pippin will remove a burden, but if you win, you may add one for the Prancing Pony.  You can heal your Frodo with Arwen and Legolas, so try to keep him at 1 wound or less vs. Nazgul, 2 or less vs. Isengard Orcs.  And above all, keep your men alive!  <br>
<br>
Questions:<br>
Why start Pippin over Merry?<br>
<br>
Merry is as good of a choice, if you find yourself needing to heal Frodo, Merry Friend to Sam can be switched.  I just like to bid at least 1, so Pippin is my choice.  He usually is fodder anyway, while you set up.<br>
<br>
<br>
Why no Sam?<br>
<br>
After playing Superfellowship, I found that you give them too much twilight, and even if they don&#39;t touch your fellowship, they get shadow out of their hands, and they have a strong fellowship.  Sam was one of the guys that didn&#39;t make the cut, along with Merry, Gandalf, and Gimli.  But if burden decks are popular in your area, play Sam over Arwen or Legolas.<br>
<br>
<br>
Why Heir to the White City?<br>
<br>
Maybe I just like using new cards, but his ability to remove pool can keep your opponent down to one less minion many times, which keeps you from losing battles with your lesser characters.  Other than the men, the other companions are not expected to win.<br>
<br>
Why Arwen, Elven Rider?<br>
<br>
She is a Ranger, which helps if all hell has broken loose and someone has died.  You can play No Stranger on her, she works with Pathfinder and site 7, and if worse comes to worse, you can pitch cards to save Frodo, or to get dead cards out of hand.<br>
<br>
Why Uruviel?<br>
<br>
With Boromir&#39;s Horn and your site 6, she is an 11!  and Celeborn a 12!<br>
<br>
<br>
Shadow:  Seems to be the best version out now, but if you know of any changes let me know! <br>
<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  I know this is not a perfect deck, but I would like constructive input on how to make it better.  I would like to thank the following:<br>
<br>
Josh Bader, for inspiration on the decklist<br>
Nick Jenniges, Josh Slibernick, and Kohman for helping test, we have many beatings to go before GenCon!<br>
<br>
Scott Poster<br>
&quot;Master P&quot;<br>
Rider of Rohan, Central MN<br>
